ACT:
 Income Tax Act 1961-S. 179-Scope of-Resolution for winding up of company passed before the coming into force of the Act-I.T.O. issued notices to Managing Director & Director to pay large tax arrears due from the company - Notice if valid.
 Section 179 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (before it was amended in 1975) provided that when any private company is wound up after the commencement of the Act and any tax assessed on the company whether before or in the course of or after its liquidation in respect of any income of any previous year cannot be recovered, then, every person who was a director of the private company at any time during the relevant previous year shall be jointly and severally liable for the payment of such tax.
 
